This document describes how to perform a Tux Football release.

Prequisits
-Wall -Wextra

cppcheck --force --enable=all src/ -I /usr/include/SDL/

Linux
-----

Build the game by
# make distclean; ./autogen.sh && make distcheck

Ubuntu / Debian
---------------

initial layout using
# dh_make -s -n -p tuxfootball_0.3.0 -e egore911@egore911.de -f tuxfootball-0.3.0.tar.gz

debchange to note changes

fakeroot debian/rules clean
fakeroot debian/rules build
fakeroot debian/rules binary 

Windows
-------

Download:
- http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/release/SDL_mixer-1.2.11.zip
- http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/release/SDL_mixer-1.2.11-win32.zip
- http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_image/release/SDL_image-1.2.10.zip
- http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_image/release/SDL_image-1.2.10-win32.zip
- http://www.libsdl.org/release/SDL-devel-1.2.14-mingw32.tar.gz

Extract DLLs to ./lib
Extract Includes to ./lib

Install the "codeblocks with mingw package" in wine

Compile using "Release" target

mkdir tuxfootball-0.3.0
cp bin/Release/tuxfootball.exe tuxfootball-0.3.0
cp lib/*.dll tuxfootball-0.3.0
mkdir -p tuxfootball-0.3.0/data/graphics
cp data/graphics/*.png tuxfootball-0.3.0/data/graphics
cp -r data/graphics/team1 tuxfootball-0.3.0/data/graphics
cp -r data/graphics/team2 tuxfootball-0.3.0/data/graphics
cp -r data/sound tuxfootball-0.3.0/data
zip -r -9 tuxfootball-0.3.0.zip tuxfootball-0.3.0

Open tuxfootball.iss using InnoSetup
cp bin/setup.exe tuxfootball-0.3.0.exe
